      "content": "i was just looking at some photos of deep space and it hit me. like, in a few billion years the sun dies, then eventually everything just goes cold and dark. everything we do, every single thing we feel or struggle for, it's just... nothing. it's all just a temporary glitch in a void that doesn't care. it makes everything feel so pointless.",
